title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter not displaying in data set dialog
description: When calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, in the query result page, no data is returned and the output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
OB: The output parameter is not displayed in the edit data set dialog.
EB: The output parameter should be displayed in the edit data set dialog.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Call a stored procedure from an Oracle database. 
2. Check the query result page. No data should be returned. 
3. Open the edit data set dialog and verify that the output parameter is not displayed.
